{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "reduce-sub-agent-dispatch-artifact-duplication", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "Intent clarity rated HIGH because goal is unambiguous; but Acceptance signal bundles four distinct goals beyond duplication-reduction (snapshot consistency, worktree path resolution, structured Read-failure signal, test coverage). The clarified intent conflates token-reduction with correctness-semantics goals.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness rated HIGH; but constraint #4 inherits implicit-today concurrent-write semantics and asks implementer to define them, which is scope expansion not bounding. Size-gated-hybrid sub-question is another unbounded design axis.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment rated HIGH with No conflicts; but assessment cites multi-agent.md and project.md without quoting alignment. DR-1's mechanism was tightened during critical-review with known TOCTOU and worktree-cwd pitfalls the child inherits as constraints but does not resolve.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Complexity rated complex with reasoning about three candidate mechanisms; but source lists Other models surfaced during research plus a non-binding recommendation, giving the design space properties of an unbounded spike rather than complex-but-bounded implementation.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Parent epic alignment: epic body frames as token-cost (N+2 copies, ~3-15k tokens); child Why it matters pivots to correctness corollary (snapshot drift, concurrent modification) not present in epic body. Child has expanded the parent's token-waste finding into a correctness-refactor scope.", "origin": "alignment"}, {"text": "Parent epic alignment: epic body says critical-review tightened DR-1's mechanism (worktree cwd; TOCTOU pin; path-argument invocation), which only refined path-Read approach; child re-opens three-way mechanism choice between path-Read, hash+path, and pre-slicing.", "origin": "alignment"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 1, "dismiss": 5, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Propagated alignment consideration to research phase: validate whether snapshot-drift during parallel fan-out is an observed failure mode or hypothetical, since epic evidence base is token-cost measurement not concurrent-write incidents."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "The bundled goals are coherent corollaries of the dispatch-mechanism refactor — once inlining stops, snapshot semantics, Read-failure handling, and worktree path resolution must be defined as part of the same mechanism change. The ticket intentionally bundles them as one constraint set."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "The constraint bounds the requirement (must define behavior) not the answer; defining implicit-today semantics is appropriate research scope. Size-gated-hybrid is a research sub-question, not a scope expansion."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "Constraints #2 (worktree-cwd) and #4 (concurrent-write) explicitly inherit the audit critical-review tightening of DR-1; the child ticket addresses these pitfalls as research-phase requirements rather than leaving them unaddressed."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Design space is narrowed by 5 explicit constraints and Reviewer-2 prior committed recommendation that serves as input. Three enumerated candidate mechanisms plus other models is a bounded research scope, not an unbounded spike — the constraints prune the design space significantly."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "Child correctly defers mechanism choice to its own research phase per the epic's documented pattern (cf. lifecycle-state-storage rethink leaving storage choice open for its child ticket). The treat-recommendation-as-input language is consistent with the epic's intent that mechanism commitments happen at child-ticket research phases."}], "status": "ok"}
